{% faqAccordion title="Leaders in Training FAQ" %}
{% faqItem
   question="How old do I have to be a part of Leaders In Training?"
   answer="You must have completed at least your first year of high school and desire a growing, personal relationship with God." /%}
{% faqItem
   question="How many weeks can I be a part of Leaders In Training?"
   answer="We ask that Leaders In Training applicants serve at least two weeks over the course of the summer. The LIT program is divided into three different 2-week sessions. We ask that you commit to one full session. If you are interested in a second session, you may apply for two sessions, but we cannot guarantee multiple sessions." /%}
{% faqItem
   question="Do I get paid to be a part of Leaders In Training?"
   answer="No, L.I.T is a volunteer opportunity. Housing and all your meals are provided during your week at camp." /%}
{% faqItem
   question="When will I find out which weeks I will be volunteering?"
   answer="Applications will be reviewed and applicants will be notified by mid-May. If accepted, you will be required to attend Staff Training Day in June." /%}
{% faqItem
   question="What does a day of Leaders In Training look like?"
   answer="Every morning before breakfast, the L.I.Ts spend some time doing a personal devotion. At each meal you sit with the campers and eat with them, build relationships, and encourage positive life skills at the table. After each meal, the L.I.Ts are responsible for cleaning the Dining Room and doing the dishes. After breakfast, the cabin bathrooms are cleaned by the L.I.Ts. Then they engage in a Bible Study. Each day, you will either do a work project in the morning and participate in the afternoon activities with the campers or the other way around. At Snack Shack, the L.I.Ts run the store and hand out the snacks. L.I.Ts participate in the evening game and Chapel each night. And before bed, the L.I.Ts gets together for reflection and prayer." /%}
{% /faqAccordion %}

